ook is an exploration of the subsequent impact of the program—how it has influenced debates about euthanasia and related ethical issues across decades. In a sweeping narrative, she shows how both the dismissive attitude that many commentators have had to the program and the assumption by many disability activists that it is relevant to every disability-related ethical issue (i.e., the Nazi analogy) continue to have harmful, even catastrophic, repercussions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEugenicsxHistoryy20th century. 0aEuthanasiaxSocial aspects. 0aInvoluntary treatment. 0aPeople with disabilitiesxNazi persecution. 7aHISTORY / Holocaust.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079770108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079771840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978168585977040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781685859770423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781685859770/original  a978-3-11-079770-1  Lynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-079771-8  Lynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles